{"descriptions":[{"id":1428,"title":"Sekhang Drupé Gyeltsen Mingyur Ling Introduction","content":"\u003cdiv class=\"essay-body\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"essay-head2\"\u003e\u003ctable\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chapter\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eA Survey of Bonpo Monasteries\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"eng\"\u003eby \u003c/span\u003eDondrup Lhagyal, \n\t\tPhuntso Tsering Sharyul, \n\t\tTsering Thar, \n\t\tCharles Ramble and Marietta Kind\u003c!--(l)--\u003e\u003cbr/\u003eEdited by Samten G. Karmay and Yasuhiko Nagano \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"width: 100%; text-align: right;\" align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"copyright\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"eng\"\u003e Copyright \u0026copy; 2003. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"eng\" id=\"permission\"\u003eReproduced with permission from the authors \u003cbr xmlns:str=\"http://exslt.org/strings\"/\u003eunder the \u003ca href=\"/tools/licenses.php#essay=/thl/text-license/\" class=\"thl-poplink\"\u003eTHL Digital Text License\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"b6-3\"\u003eReb gong \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n                  \u003ch3 id=\"b6-3-11\"\u003e(110) Dar grong Temple\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-1\"\u003e1. Name\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003egSas khang sGrub pa\u0026rsquo;i rgyal mtshan mi \u0026rsquo;gyur gling\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-2\"\u003e2. Location\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eDar grong village\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-3\"\u003e5. Number of practitioners\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eThere are twenty-seven Bonpo Tantric practitioners in the temple.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-4\"\u003e8 / 9. Rituals\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eKun bzang and Tshe dbang alternately on the 10th of each month. Kun bzang,\n                        \u0026rsquo;Bum pa and sPyi \u0026rsquo;dul from the 16th to the 20th day of the 1st month. Kun\n                        bzang and sPyi \u0026rsquo;dul from the 16th to the 20th day of the 12th month.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-5\"\u003e12. Local community\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eThe community comprises twenty families (one hundred and eighty people\n                        altogether).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-6\"\u003e13. Local festivals\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eThe \u003cspan xmlns:str=\"http://exslt.org/strings\" style=\"font-style: italic;\" class=\"\"\u003ela btsas\u003c/span\u003e of \u0026rsquo;U gzur located 3 km from the temple,\n                        at the center of the mountain facing the temple and propitited on the 17th\n                        day of the 6th month.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-11-7\"\u003e14. Economic occupation of the local people \u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eAgriculture\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n               \u003ctable xmlns:str=\"http://exslt.org/strings\" cellspacing=\"8\" align=\"center\" class=\"navarrows\"\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"leftcell\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"backarrow\" title=\"Previous Section\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-left.gif\" title=\"Previous Section\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd class=\"midcell\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"uparrow\" title=\